273 enum AuraRemoveMode
274 {
275  AURA_REMOVE_BY_DEFAULT,
276  AURA_REMOVE_BY_STACK, // at replace by similar aura
277  AURA_REMOVE_BY_CANCEL,
278  AURA_REMOVE_BY_DISPEL,
279  AURA_REMOVE_BY_DEATH,
280  AURA_REMOVE_BY_DELETE, // use for speedup and prevent unexpected effects at player logout/pet unsummon (must be used _only_ after save), delete.

282  AURA_REMOVE_BY_EXPIRE, // at duration end

351 enum DeathState
352 {
353  ALIVE = 0, // show as alive
354  JUST_DIED = 1, // temporary state at die, for creature auto converted to CORPSE, for player at next update call
355  CORPSE = 2, // corpse state, for player this also meaning that player not leave corpse
356  DEAD = 3, // for creature despawned state (corpse despawned), for player CORPSE/DEAD not clear way switches (FIXME), and use m_deathtimer > 0 check for real corpse state
357  JUST_ALIVED = 4, // temporary state at resurrection, for creature auto converted to ALIVE, for player at next update call
358 };

360 // internal state flags for some auras and movement generators, other.
361 enum UnitState
362 {
363  // persistent state (applied by aura/etc until expire)
364  UNIT_STAT_MELEE_ATTACKING = 0x00000001, // unit is melee attacking someone Unit::Attack
365  UNIT_STAT_LOGOUT_TIMER = 0x00000002, // Unit is logging out
366  UNIT_STAT_FEIGN_DEATH = 0x00000004, // Unit::SetFeignDeath - a successful feign death is currently active
367  UNIT_STAT_STUNNED = 0x00000008, // Aura::HandleAuraModStun
368  UNIT_STAT_ROOT = 0x00000010, // Aura::HandleAuraModRoot
369  UNIT_STAT_ISOLATED = 0x00000020, // area auras do not affect other players, Aura::HandleAuraModSchoolImmunity
370  UNIT_STAT_POSSESSED = 0x00000040, // Aura::HandleAuraModPossess (duplicates UNIT_FLAG_POSSESSED)
371 
372  // movement generators begin:
373  UNIT_STAT_TAXI_FLIGHT = 0x00000080, // TaxiMovementGenerator on stack
374  UNIT_STAT_PROPELLED = 0x00000100, // EffectMovementGenerator on stack
375  UNIT_STAT_PANIC = 0x00000200, // PanicMovementGenerator on stack
376  UNIT_STAT_RETREATING = 0x00000400, // RetreatMovementGenerator on stack
377  UNIT_STAT_DISTRACTED = 0x00000800, // DistractedMovementGenerator on stack
378  UNIT_STAT_STAY = 0x00001000, // StayMovementGenerator on stack
379  UNIT_STAT_CONFUSED = 0x00002000, // ConfusedMovementGenerator on stack
380  UNIT_STAT_CONFUSED_MOVE = 0x00004000, // ^ - spline dispatched
381  UNIT_STAT_ROAMING = 0x00008000, // Point/Retreat/Stay/Wander/Waypoint/Effect MovementGenerator on stack
382  UNIT_STAT_ROAMING_MOVE = 0x00010000, // ^ - spline dispatched
383  UNIT_STAT_CHASE = 0x00020000, // ChaseMovementGenerator on stack
384  UNIT_STAT_CHASE_MOVE = 0x00040000, // ^ - spline dispatched
385  UNIT_STAT_FOLLOW = 0x00080000, // FollowMovementGenerator on stack
386  UNIT_STAT_FOLLOW_MOVE = 0x00100000, // ^ - spline dispatched
387  UNIT_STAT_FLEEING = 0x00200000, // FleeingMovementGenerator/PanicMovementGenerator on stack
388  UNIT_STAT_FLEEING_MOVE = 0x00400000, // ^ - spline dispatched
389  // movemement generators end
390 
391  UNIT_STAT_CHANNELING = 0x00800000,
392 
393  // High-Level states (usually only with Creatures)
394  UNIT_STAT_NO_COMBAT_MOVEMENT = 0x01000000, // Combat Movement for MoveChase stopped
395  UNIT_STAT_NO_FOLLOW_MOVEMENT = 0x02000000,
396  UNIT_STAT_RUNNING = 0x04000000, // SetRun for waypoints and such
397  UNIT_STAT_WAYPOINT_PAUSED = 0x08000000, // Waypoint-Movement paused genericly (ie by script)
398 
399  UNIT_STAT_IGNORE_PATHFINDING = 0x10000000, // do not use pathfinding in any MovementGenerator
400  UNIT_STAT_AI_ROOT = 0x20000000, // root but from AI script
401 
402  // masks (only for check)
403 
404  // can't move currently
405  UNIT_STAT_CAN_NOT_MOVE = UNIT_STAT_ROOT | UNIT_STAT_STUNNED | UNIT_STAT_LOGOUT_TIMER | UNIT_STAT_FEIGN_DEATH | UNIT_STAT_AI_ROOT,
406 
407  // stay by different reasons
408  UNIT_STAT_NOT_MOVE = UNIT_STAT_ROOT | UNIT_STAT_STUNNED | UNIT_STAT_LOGOUT_TIMER | UNIT_STAT_FEIGN_DEATH |
409  UNIT_STAT_DISTRACTED | UNIT_STAT_AI_ROOT,
410 
411  // stay or scripted movement for effect( = in player case you can't move by client command)
412  UNIT_STAT_NO_FREE_MOVE = UNIT_STAT_ROOT | UNIT_STAT_STUNNED | UNIT_STAT_LOGOUT_TIMER | UNIT_STAT_FEIGN_DEATH |
413  UNIT_STAT_TAXI_FLIGHT |
414  UNIT_STAT_CONFUSED | UNIT_STAT_FLEEING | UNIT_STAT_PROPELLED | UNIT_STAT_AI_ROOT,
415 
416  // not react at move in sight or other
417  UNIT_STAT_CAN_NOT_REACT = UNIT_STAT_STUNNED | UNIT_STAT_LOGOUT_TIMER | UNIT_STAT_FEIGN_DEATH |
418  UNIT_STAT_CONFUSED | UNIT_STAT_FLEEING | UNIT_STAT_RETREATING,
419 
420  // AI disabled by some reason
421  UNIT_STAT_LOST_CONTROL = UNIT_STAT_CONFUSED | UNIT_STAT_FLEEING | UNIT_STAT_POSSESSED,
422 
423  // above 2 state cases
424  UNIT_STAT_CAN_NOT_REACT_OR_LOST_CONTROL = UNIT_STAT_CAN_NOT_REACT | UNIT_STAT_LOST_CONTROL,
425 
426  // masks (for check or reset)
427 
428  // for real move using movegen check and stop (except unstoppable flight)
429  UNIT_STAT_MOVING = UNIT_STAT_ROAMING_MOVE | UNIT_STAT_CHASE_MOVE | UNIT_STAT_FOLLOW_MOVE | UNIT_STAT_FLEEING_MOVE,
430 
431  UNIT_STAT_RUNNING_STATE = UNIT_STAT_CHASE_MOVE | UNIT_STAT_FLEEING_MOVE | UNIT_STAT_RUNNING,
432 
433  UNIT_STAT_ALL_STATE = 0xFFFFFFFF,
434  UNIT_STAT_ALL_DYN_STATES = UNIT_STAT_ALL_STATE & ~(UNIT_STAT_NO_COMBAT_MOVEMENT | UNIT_STAT_RUNNING | UNIT_STAT_WAYPOINT_PAUSED | UNIT_STAT_IGNORE_PATHFINDING),
435 };

490 enum UnitVisibility
491 {
492  VISIBILITY_OFF = 0, // absolute, not detectable, GM-like, can see all other
493  VISIBILITY_ON = 1,
494  VISIBILITY_GROUP_STEALTH = 2, // detect chance, seen and can see group members
495  VISIBILITY_GROUP_INVISIBILITY = 3, // invisibility, can see and can be seen only another invisible unit or invisible detection unit, set only if not stealthed, and in checks not used (mask used instead)
496  VISIBILITY_GROUP_NO_DETECT = 4, // state just at stealth apply for update Grid state. Don't remove, otherwise stealth spells will break
497  VISIBILITY_REMOVE_CORPSE = 5 // special totally not detectable visibility for force delete object while removing a corpse
498 };

500 // Value masks for UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS
501 enum UnitFlags
502 {
503  UNIT_FLAG_UNK_0 = 0x00000001, // Movement checks disabled, likely paired with loss of client control packet. We use it to add custom cliffwalking to GM mode until actual usecases will be known.
504  UNIT_FLAG_SPAWNING = 0x00000002, // not attackable
505  UNIT_FLAG_CLIENT_CONTROL_LOST = 0x00000004, // Generic unspecified loss of control initiated by server script, movement checks disabled, paired with loss of client control packet.
506  UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED = 0x00000008, // players, pets, totems, guardians, companions, charms, any units associated with players
507  UNIT_FLAG_RENAME = 0x00000010,
508  UNIT_FLAG_PREPARATION = 0x00000020, // don't take reagents for spells with SPELL_ATTR_EX5_NO_REAGENT_WHILE_PREP
509  UNIT_FLAG_UNK_6 = 0x00000040,
510  UNIT_FLAG_NOT_ATTACKABLE_1 = 0x00000080, // ?? (UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE | UNIT_FLAG_NOT_ATTACKABLE_1) is NON_PVP_ATTACKABLE
511  UNIT_FLAG_IMMUNE_TO_PLAYER = 0x00000100, // Target is immune to players
512  UNIT_FLAG_IMMUNE_TO_NPC = 0x00000200, // Target is immune to Non-Player Characters
513  UNIT_FLAG_LOOTING = 0x00000400, // loot animation
514  UNIT_FLAG_PET_IN_COMBAT = 0x00000800, // in combat?, 2.0.8
515  UNIT_FLAG_PVP_DEPRECATED = 0x00001000, // changed in 3.0.3
516  UNIT_FLAG_SILENCED = 0x00002000, // silenced, 2.1.1
517  UNIT_FLAG_UNK_14 = 0x00004000, // 2.0.8
518  UNIT_FLAG_SWIMMING = 0x00008000, // related to jerky movement in water?
519  UNIT_FLAG_UNTARGETABLE = 0x00010000, // is not targetable by attack or spell
520  UNIT_FLAG_PACIFIED = 0x00020000, // 3.0.3 ok
521  UNIT_FLAG_STUNNED = 0x00040000, // Unit is a subject to stun, turn and strafe movement disabled
522  UNIT_FLAG_IN_COMBAT = 0x00080000,
523  UNIT_FLAG_TAXI_FLIGHT = 0x00100000, // Unit is on taxi, paired with a duplicate loss of client control packet (likely a legacy serverside hack). Disables any spellcasts not allowed in taxi flight client-side.
524  UNIT_FLAG_DISARMED = 0x00200000, // 3.0.3, disable melee spells casting..., "Required melee weapon" added to melee spells tooltip.
525  UNIT_FLAG_CONFUSED = 0x00400000, // Unit is a subject to confused movement, movement checks disabled, paired with loss of client control packet.
526  UNIT_FLAG_FLEEING = 0x00800000, // Unit is a subject to fleeing movement, movement checks disabled, paired with loss of client control packet.
527  UNIT_FLAG_POSSESSED = 0x01000000, // Unit is under remote control by another unit, movement checks disabled, paired with loss of client control packet. New master is allowed to use melee attack and can't select this unit via mouse in the world (as if it was own character).
528  UNIT_FLAG_UNINTERACTIBLE = 0x02000000,
529  UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE = 0x04000000,
530  UNIT_FLAG_MOUNT = 0x08000000,
531  UNIT_FLAG_UNK_28 = 0x10000000,
532  UNIT_FLAG_PREVENT_ANIM = 0x20000000, // used in Feing Death spell

534  UNIT_FLAG_IMMUNE = 0x80000000

676 // A little helper func for a nice attack table debug output
677 inline const char* UnitCombatDieSideText(UnitCombatDieSide side)
678 {
679  switch (side)
680  {
681  case UNIT_COMBAT_DIE_MISS: return "MISS";
682  case UNIT_COMBAT_DIE_RESIST: return "RESIST";
683  case UNIT_COMBAT_DIE_DODGE: return "DODGE";
684  case UNIT_COMBAT_DIE_PARRY: return "PARRY";
685  case UNIT_COMBAT_DIE_DEFLECT: return "DEFLECT";
686  case UNIT_COMBAT_DIE_BLOCK: return "BLOCK";
687  case UNIT_COMBAT_DIE_GLANCE: return "GLANCE";
688  case UNIT_COMBAT_DIE_CRIT: return "CRIT";
689  case UNIT_COMBAT_DIE_CRUSH: return "CRUSH";
690  case UNIT_COMBAT_DIE_HIT: return "HIT";
691  }
692  return "INVALID";
693 }

871 enum ActiveStates

889 #define UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(X) (uint32(X) & 0x00FFFFFF)
890 #define UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_TYPE(X) ((uint32(X) & 0xFF000000) >> 24)
891 #define MAX_UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION_VALUE (0x00FFFFFF+1)
892 #define MAKE_UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON(A,T) (uint32(A) | (uint32(T) << 24))
893 
894 struct UnitActionBarEntry
895 {
896  UnitActionBarEntry() : packedData(uint32(ACT_DISABLED) << 24) {}
897 
898  uint32 packedData;
899 
900  // helper
901  ActiveStates GetType() const { return ActiveStates(UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_TYPE(packedData)); }
902  uint32 GetAction() const { return UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(packedData); }
903  bool IsActionBarForSpell() const
904  {
905  ActiveStates Type = GetType();
906  return Type == ACT_DISABLED || Type == ACT_ENABLED || Type == ACT_PASSIVE;
907  }
908 
909  void SetActionAndType(uint32 action, ActiveStates type)
910  {
911  packedData = MAKE_UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON(action, type);
912  }
913 
914  void SetType(ActiveStates type)
915  {
916  packedData = MAKE_UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON(UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(packedData), type);
917  }
918 
919  void SetAction(uint32 action)
920  {
921  packedData = (packedData & 0xFF000000) | UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(action);
922  }
923 };

1090 // Selection method used by SelectAttackingTarget
1091 enum AttackingTarget
1092 {
1093  ATTACKING_TARGET_RANDOM = 0, // Just selects a random target
1094  ATTACKING_TARGET_TOPAGGRO, // Selects targes from top aggro to bottom
1095  ATTACKING_TARGET_BOTTOMAGGRO, // Selects targets from bottom aggro to top
1096  ATTACKING_TARGET_NEAREST_BY, // Selects the nearest by target
1097  ATTACKING_TARGET_FARTHEST_AWAY, // Selects the farthest away target
1098  ATTACKING_TARGET_ALL_SUITABLE,
1099 };

1101 enum SelectFlags
1102 {
1103  SELECT_FLAG_IN_LOS = 0x0001, // Default Selection Requirement for Spell-targets
1104  SELECT_FLAG_PLAYER = 0x0002,
1105  SELECT_FLAG_POWER_MANA = 0x0004, // For Energy based spells, like manaburn
1106  SELECT_FLAG_POWER_RAGE = 0x0008,
1107  SELECT_FLAG_POWER_ENERGY = 0x0010,
1108  SELECT_FLAG_IN_MELEE_RANGE = 0x0040,
1109  SELECT_FLAG_NOT_IN_MELEE_RANGE = 0x0080,
1110  SELECT_FLAG_HAS_AURA = 0x0100,
1111  SELECT_FLAG_NOT_AURA = 0x0200,
1112  SELECT_FLAG_RANGE_RANGE = 0x0400, // For direct targeted abilities like charge or frostbolt but need custom data
1113  SELECT_FLAG_RANGE_AOE_RANGE = 0x0800, // For AOE targeted abilities like frost nova but need custom data
1114  SELECT_FLAG_POWER_NOT_MANA = 0x1000, // Used in some dungeon encounters
1115  SELECT_FLAG_USE_EFFECT_RADIUS = 0x2000, // For AOE targeted abilities which have correct data in effect index 0
1116  SELECT_FLAG_SKIP_TANK = 0x4000, // Not GetVictim - tank is not always top threat
1117  SELECT_FLAG_CASTING = 0x8000, // Selects only targets that are casting
1118  SELECT_FLAG_SKIP_CUSTOM =0x10000, // skips custom target
1119  SELECT_FLAG_NOT_IMMUNE =0x20000,
1120  SELECT_FLAG_USE_EFFECT_RADIUS_OF_TRIGGERED_SPELL = 0x40000 // For AOE targeted abilities which have correct data in triggered spell effect index 0
1121 };

1302  bool _addAttacker(Unit* pAttacker) //< (Internal Use) must be called only from Unit::Attack(Unit*)
1303  {
1304  AttackerSet::const_iterator itr = m_attackers.find(pAttacker);
1305  if (itr == m_attackers.end())
1306  {
1307  m_attackers.insert(pAttacker);
1308  return true;
1309  }
1310  return false;
1311  }
1312  void _removeAttacker(Unit* pAttacker) //< (Internal Use) must be called only from Unit::AttackStop()
1313  {
1314  m_attackers.erase(pAttacker);
1315  }

1320

1322  return *(m_attackers.begin());
1323 
1324  return nullptr;
1325  }

1746  template<typename Func>
1747  bool HasAuraHolder(Func func) const
1748  {
1749  auto const& Auras = GetSpellAuraHolderMap();
1750  for (auto itr = Auras.begin(); itr != Auras.end(); ++itr)
1751  {
1752  SpellAuraHolder* holder = itr->second;
1753  if (func(holder))
1754  return true;
1755  }
1756  return false;
1757  }
1758 
1759  template<typename Func>
1760  bool HasAura(Func func, AuraType type) const
1761  {
1762  auto const& Auras = GetAurasByType(type);
1763  for (auto itr = Auras.begin(); itr != Auras.end(); ++itr)
1764  {
1765  if (func(*itr))
1766  return true;
1767  }
1768  return false;
1769  }

2808 
2809 template<typename Func>
2810 void Unit::CallForAllControlledUnits(Func const& func, uint32 controlledMask)
2811 {
2812  if (controlledMask & CONTROLLED_PET)
2813  if (Pet* pet = GetPet())
2814  func(pet);
2815 
2816  if (controlledMask & CONTROLLED_MINIPET)
2817  if (Pet* mini = GetMiniPet())
2818  func(mini);
2819 
2820  if (controlledMask & CONTROLLED_GUARDIANS)
2821  {
2822  for (m_guardianPetsIterator = m_guardianPets.begin(); m_guardianPetsIterator != m_guardianPets.end();)
2823  if (Pet* guardian = GetMap()->GetPet(*(m_guardianPetsIterator++)))
2824  func(guardian);
2825  }
2826 
2827  if (controlledMask & CONTROLLED_TOTEMS)
2828  {
2829  for (int i = 0; i < MAX_TOTEM_SLOT; ++i)
2830  if (Unit* totem = _GetTotem(TotemSlot(i)))
2831  func(totem);
2832  }
2833 
2834  if (controlledMask & CONTROLLED_CHARM)
2835  {
2836  if (Unit* charm = GetCharm())
2837  func(charm);
2838 
2839  for (GuidSet::const_iterator itr = m_charmedUnitsPrivate.begin(); itr != m_charmedUnitsPrivate.end();)
2840  if (Unit* charmed = _GetUnit(*(itr++)))
2841  func(charmed);
2842  }
2843 }
2844 
2845 template<typename Func>
2846 bool Unit::CheckAllControlledUnits(Func const& func, uint32 controlledMask) const
2847 {
2848  if (controlledMask & CONTROLLED_PET)
2849  if (Pet const* pet = GetPet())
2850  if (func(pet))
2851  return true;
2852 
2853  if (controlledMask & CONTROLLED_MINIPET)
2854  if (Pet const* mini = GetMiniPet())
2855  if (func(mini))
2856  return true;
2857 
2858  if (controlledMask & CONTROLLED_GUARDIANS)
2859  {
2860  for (auto m_guardianPet : m_guardianPets)
2861  if (Pet* guardian = GetMap()->GetPet(m_guardianPet))
2862  if (func(guardian))
2863  return true;
2864  }
2865 
2866  if (controlledMask & CONTROLLED_TOTEMS)
2867  {
2868  for (int i = 0; i < MAX_TOTEM_SLOT; ++i)
2869  if (Unit const* totem = _GetTotem(TotemSlot(i)))
2870  if (func(totem))
2871  return true;
2872  }
2873 
2874  if (controlledMask & CONTROLLED_CHARM)
2875  {
2876  if (Unit const* charm = GetCharm())
2877  if (func(charm))
2878  return true;
2879 
2880  for (GuidSet::const_iterator itr = m_charmedUnitsPrivate.begin(); itr != m_charmedUnitsPrivate.end();)
2881  if (Unit const* charmed = _GetUnit(*(itr++)))
2882  if (func(charmed))
2883  return true;
2884  }
2885 
2886  return false;
2887 }

2889 // Helper for targets nearest to the spell target
2890 // The spell target is always first unless there is a target at _completely_ the same position (unbelievable case)
2891 struct TargetDistanceOrderNear
2892 {
2893  WorldObject const* m_mainTarget;
2894  DistanceCalculation m_distcalc;
2895 
2896  TargetDistanceOrderNear(WorldObject const* target, DistanceCalculation distcalc = DIST_CALC_NONE) : m_mainTarget(target), m_distcalc(distcalc) {}
2897  // functor for operator ">"
2898  bool operator()(WorldObject const* _Left, WorldObject const* _Right) const
2899  {
2900  return m_mainTarget->GetDistanceOrder(_Left, _Right, m_distcalc);
2901  }
2902 };
2903 
2904 // Helper for targets furthest away to the spell target
2905 // The spell target is always first unless there is a target at _completely_ the same position (unbelievable case)
2906 struct TargetDistanceOrderFarAway
2907 {
2908  WorldObject const* m_mainTarget;
2909  DistanceCalculation m_distcalc;
2910  TargetDistanceOrderFarAway(WorldObject const* target, DistanceCalculation distcalc = DIST_CALC_NONE) : m_mainTarget(target), m_distcalc(distcalc) {}
2911  // functor for operator "<"
2912  bool operator()(WorldObject const* _Left, WorldObject const* _Right) const
2913  {
2914  return !m_mainTarget->GetDistanceOrder(_Left, _Right, m_distcalc);
2915  }
2916 };
2917 
2918 struct LowestHPNearestOrder
2919 {
2920  WorldObject const* m_mainTarget;
2921  DistanceCalculation m_distcalc;
2922 
2923  LowestHPNearestOrder(WorldObject const* target, DistanceCalculation distcalc = DIST_CALC_NONE) : m_mainTarget(target), m_distcalc(distcalc) {}
2924  // functor for operator ">"
2925  bool operator()(Unit const* _Left, Unit const* _Right) const
2926  {
2927  if (_Left->GetHealthPercent() == _Right->GetHealthPercent())
2928  return m_mainTarget->GetDistanceOrder(_Left, _Right, m_distcalc);
2929  return _Left->GetHealthPercent() < _Right->GetHealthPercent();
2930  }
2931 };
